Package: XboostingMM
Type: Package
Title: Extreme Gradient Boosting Mix Effects Model: Machine learning algorithm for hierarchical data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Espinoza", "Marco", email = "espinozamarco70@gmail.com",
  role = "aut")
URL: https://github.com/antonioespinoza98/XboostingMM
BugReports: https://github.com/antonioespinoza98/XboostingMM/issues
Maintainer: Marco Espinoza <espinozamarco70@gmail.com>
Description: XboostingMM is a powerful package that combines 
    the strengths of Extreme Gradient Boosting (XGBoost) and mixed-effects models, 
    offering a robust semi-parametric algorithm. 
    Designed to provide the best of both worlds, it leverages the speed, scalability, 
    and performance of XGBoost while incorporating the adaptability of mixed-effects models. 
    This powerful combination allows for effective handling of hierarchical data 
    and provides flexible estimation techniques that can bypass traditional linear model assumptions, 
    making it particularly useful for Small Area Estimation and other complex data scenarios.
